Class Result

java.lang.Object
org.tensorflow.Result
All Implemented Interfaces:
AutoCloseable, Iterable<Map.Entry<String,Tensor>>
public final class Result extends Object implements AutoCloseable, Iterable<Map.Entry<String,Tensor>>
An AutoCloseable wrapper around a Map containing Tensors.

When this is closed it closes all the Tensors inside it. If you maintain a reference to a value after this object has been closed it will throw an IllegalStateException upon access.

This class is not thread-safe with respect to the close operation. Multiple closers or one thread closing a tensor while another is reading may throw exceptions.

Note this class is used to manage the lifetimes of tensors produced by the TensorFlow runtime, from sessions and function calls. It is not used as an argument to session.run or function calls as users are in control of the creation of input tensors.
